#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:4
msgid "Deprecations and Removals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:6
msgid ""
"This page lists all pytest features that are currently deprecated or have "
"been removed in past major releases. The objective is to give users a clear "
"rationale why a certain feature has been removed, and what alternatives "
"should be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:11
msgid "Deprecated Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:13
msgid ""
"Below is a complete list of all pytest features which are considered "
"deprecated. Using those features will issue :class:`_pytest.warning_types."
"PytestWarning` or subclasses, which can be filtered using :ref:`standard "
"warning filters <warnings>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:18
msgid "Internal classes accessed through ``Node``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:22
msgid ""
"Access of ``Module``, ``Function``, ``Class``, ``Instance``, ``File`` and "
"``Item`` through ``Node`` instances now issue this warning::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:25
msgid ""
"usage of Function.Module is deprecated, please use pytest.Module instead"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:27
msgid ""
"Users should just ``import pytest`` and access those objects using the "
"``pytest`` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:29 ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:62
msgid ""
"This has been documented as deprecated for years, but only now we are "
"actually emitting deprecation warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:32
msgid "``cached_setup``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:36
msgid ""
"``request.cached_setup`` was the precursor of the setup/teardown mechanism "
"available to fixtures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:38
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "範例："

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:40
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def db_session():\n"
"    return request.cached_setup(\n"
"        setup=Session.create, teardown=lambda session: session.close(), "
"scope=\"module\"\n"
"    )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:48
msgid "This should be updated to make use of standard fixture mechanisms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:50
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture(scope=\"module\")\n"
"def db_session():\n"
"    session = Session.create()\n"
"    yield session\n"
"    session.close()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:59
msgid ""
"You can consult `funcarg comparison section in the docs <https://docs.pytest."
"org/en/latest/funcarg_compare.html>`_ for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:66
msgid "Using ``Class`` in custom Collectors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:70
msgid ""
"Using objects named ``\"Class\"`` as a way to customize the type of nodes "
"that are collected in ``Collector`` subclasses has been deprecated. Users "
"instead should use ``pytest_pycollect_makeitem`` to customize node types "
"during collection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:74
msgid ""
"This issue should affect only advanced plugins who create new collection "
"types, so if you see this warning message please contact the authors so they "
"can change the code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:79
msgid "``Config.warn`` and ``Node.warn``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:83
msgid ""
"Those methods were part of the internal pytest warnings system, but since "
"``3.8`` pytest is using the builtin warning system for its own warnings, so "
"those two functions are now deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:86
msgid ""
"``Config.warn`` should be replaced by calls to the standard ``warnings."
"warn``, example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:88
msgid "config.warn(\"C1\", \"some warning\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:92
msgid "Becomes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:94
msgid "warnings.warn(pytest.PytestWarning(\"some warning\"))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:98
msgid "``Node.warn`` now supports two signatures:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:100
msgid ""
"``node.warn(PytestWarning(\"some message\"))``: is now the **recommended** "
"way to call this function. The warning instance must be a PytestWarning or "
"subclass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:103
msgid ""
"``node.warn(\"CI\", \"some message\")``: this code/message form is now "
"**deprecated** and should be converted to the warning instance form above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:107
msgid "``pytest_namespace``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:111
msgid ""
"This hook is deprecated because it greatly complicates the pytest internals "
"regarding configuration and initialization, making some bug fixes and "
"refactorings impossible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:114
msgid "Example of usage:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:116
msgid ""
"class MySymbol:\n"
"    ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def pytest_namespace():\n"
"    return {\"my_symbol\": MySymbol()}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:126
msgid ""
"Plugin authors relying on this hook should instead require that users now "
"import the plugin modules directly (with an appropriate public API)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:128
msgid ""
"As a stopgap measure, plugin authors may still inject their names into "
"pytest's namespace, usually during ``pytest_configure``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:130
msgid ""
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def pytest_configure():\n"
"    pytest.my_symbol = MySymbol()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:141
msgid "Calling fixtures directly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:145
msgid ""
"Calling a fixture function directly, as opposed to request them in a test "
"function, is deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:147
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:149
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def cell():\n"
"    return ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def full_cell():\n"
"    cell = cell()\n"
"    cell.make_full()\n"
"    return cell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:162
msgid ""
"This is a great source of confusion to new users, which will often call the "
"fixture functions and request them from test functions interchangeably, "
"which breaks the fixture resolution model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:164
msgid ""
"In those cases just request the function directly in the dependent fixture:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:166
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def cell():\n"
"    return ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def full_cell(cell):\n"
"    cell.make_full()\n"
"    return cell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:179
msgid "``Node.get_marker``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:183
msgid ""
"As part of a large :ref:`marker-revamp`, :meth:`_pytest.nodes.Node."
"get_marker` is deprecated. See :ref:`the documentation <update marker code>` "
"on tips on how to update your code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:188
msgid "record_xml_property"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:192
msgid ""
"The ``record_xml_property`` fixture is now deprecated in favor of the more "
"generic ``record_property``, which can be used by other consumers (for "
"example ``pytest-html``) to obtain custom information about the test run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:195
msgid "This is just a matter of renaming the fixture as the API is the same:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:197
msgid ""
"def test_foo(record_xml_property):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:202
msgid "Change to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:204
msgid ""
"def test_foo(record_property):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:210
msgid "pytest_plugins in non-top-level conftest files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:214
msgid ""
"Defining ``pytest_plugins`` is now deprecated in non-top-level conftest.py "
"files because they will activate referenced plugins *globally*, which is "
"surprising because for all other pytest features ``conftest.py`` files are "
"only *active* for tests at or below it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:219
msgid "Metafunc.addcall"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:223
msgid ""
":meth:`_pytest.python.Metafunc.addcall` was a precursor to the current "
"parametrized mechanism. Users should use :meth:`_pytest.python.Metafunc."
"parametrize` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:227
msgid "marks in ``pytest.mark.parametrize``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:231
msgid ""
"Applying marks to values of a ``pytest.mark.parametrize`` call is now "
"deprecated. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:233
msgid ""
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n"
"    \"a, b\", [(3, 9), pytest.mark.xfail(reason=\"flaky\")(6, 36), (10, "
"100)]\n"
")\n"
"def test_foo(a, b):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:241
msgid ""
"This code applies the ``pytest.mark.xfail(reason=\"flaky\")`` mark to the "
"``(6, 36)`` value of the above parametrization call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:244
msgid ""
"This was considered hard to read and understand, and also its implementation "
"presented problems to the code preventing further internal improvements in "
"the marks architecture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:247
msgid "To update the code, use ``pytest.param``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:249
msgid ""
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n"
"    \"a, b\",\n"
"    [(3, 9), pytest.param((6, 36), marks=pytest.mark."
"xfail(reason=\"flaky\")), (10, 100)],\n"
")\n"
"def test_foo(a, b):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:261
msgid "Passing command-line string to ``pytest.main()``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:265
msgid "Passing a command-line string to ``pytest.main()`` is deprecated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:267
msgid "pytest.main(\"-v -s\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:271
msgid "Pass a list instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:273
msgid "pytest.main([\"-v\", \"-s\"])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:278
msgid ""
"By passing a string, users expect that pytest will interpret that command-"
"line using the shell rules they are working on (for example ``bash`` or "
"``Powershell``), but this is very hard/impossible to do in a portable way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:283
msgid "``yield`` tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:287
msgid ""
"pytest supports ``yield``-style tests, where a test function actually "
"``yield`` functions and values that are then turned into proper test "
"methods. Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:290
msgid ""
"def check(x, y):\n"
"    assert x ** x == y\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test_squared():\n"
"    yield check, 2, 4\n"
"    yield check, 3, 9"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:300
msgid "This would result into two actual test functions being generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:302
msgid ""
"This form of test function doesn't support fixtures properly, and users "
"should switch to ``pytest.mark.parametrize``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:304
msgid ""
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"x, y\", [(2, 4), (3, 9)])\n"
"def test_squared(x, y):\n"
"    assert x ** x == y"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:312
msgid "``pytest_funcarg__`` prefix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:316
msgid ""
"In very early pytest versions fixtures could be defined using the "
"``pytest_funcarg__`` prefix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:318
msgid ""
"def pytest_funcarg__data():\n"
"    return SomeData()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:323
msgid "Switch over to the ``@pytest.fixture`` decorator:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:325
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def data():\n"
"    return SomeData()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:332
msgid "[pytest] section in setup.cfg files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:336
msgid ""
"``[pytest]`` sections in ``setup.cfg`` files should now be named ``[tool:"
"pytest]`` to avoid conflicts with other distutils commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:340
msgid "Result log (``--result-log``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:344
msgid ""
"The ``--resultlog`` command line option has been deprecated: it is little "
"used and there are more modern and better alternatives, for example `pytest-"
"tap <https://tappy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:348
msgid "Removed Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:350
msgid ""
"As stated in our :ref:`backwards-compatibility` policy, deprecated features "
"are removed only in major releases after an appropriate period of "
"deprecation has passed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:355
msgid "Reinterpretation mode (``--assert=reinterp``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:357 ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:369
#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:381
msgid "*Removed in version 3.0.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:359
msgid ""
"Reinterpretation mode has now been removed and only plain and rewrite mode "
"are available, consequently the ``--assert=reinterp`` option is no longer "
"available.  This also means files imported from plugins or ``conftest.py`` "
"will not benefit from improved assertions by default, you should use "
"``pytest.register_assert_rewrite()`` to explicitly turn on assertion "
"rewriting for those files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:367
msgid "Removed command-line options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:371
msgid "The following deprecated commandline options were removed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:373
msgid "``--genscript``: no longer supported;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:374
msgid "``--no-assert``: use ``--assert=plain`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:375
msgid "``--nomagic``: use ``--assert=plain`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:376
msgid "``--report``: use ``-r`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:379
msgid "py.test-X* entry points"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:383
msgid ""
"Removed all ``py.test-X*`` entry points. The versioned, suffixed entry "
"points were never documented and a leftover from a pre-virtualenv era. These "
"entry points also created broken entry points in wheels, so removing them "
"also removes a source of confusion for users."
msgstr ""
